<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56a3f329-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s935"><num value="935">§ 935.</num><heading> Coast Guard band recordings for commercial sale</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id56a3f32a-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s935/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> The Coast Guard band may produce recordings for commercial sale.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id56a3f32b-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s935/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> Amounts received as proceeds from the sale of any such recordings may be credited to applicable appropriations of the Coast Guard for expenses of the Coast Guard band.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id56a3f32c-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s935/c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content> The Secretary shall prescribe regulations governing the accounting of such proceeds.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id56a3f32d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/101/510/dA/tIII/s327/d/1">Pub. L. 101–510, div. A, title III, § 327(d)(1)</ref>, <date date="1990-11-05">Nov. 5, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/1532">104 Stat. 1532</ref>, § 640; renumbered § 935, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s107/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 107(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4205">132 Stat. 4205</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
